if(interactive()){ rm(list=ls()) library(ludic) data(RA) res_match_6y <- recordLink(data1 = RA1_6y, data2 = RA2_6y,                            eps_plus = 0.01, eps_minus = 0.01,                           aggreg_2ways ="mean",                           min_prev = 0,                           use_diff = FALSE)  res_match_11y <- recordLink(data1 = RA1_11y, data2 = RA2_11y,                             eps_plus = 0.01, eps_minus = 0.01,                            aggreg_2ways ="mean",                            min_prev = 0,                            use_diff = FALSE)   print.res_matching <- function(res, threshold=0.9, ref=silverstandard_truematches){  have_match_row <- rowSums(res>threshold)  have_match_col <- colSums(res>threshold)  bestmatched_pairs_all <- cbind.data.frame(    "D1"=rownames(res)[apply(res[,which(have_match_col>0), drop=FALSE], 2, which.max)],    "D2"=names(have_match_col)[which(have_match_col>0)]  )  nTM_all <- nrow(ref)  nP_all <- nrow(bestmatched_pairs_all)  TPR_all <- sum(apply(bestmatched_pairs_all, 1, paste0, collapse="")                  %in% apply(ref, 1, paste0, collapse=""))/nTM_all  PPV_all <- sum(apply(bestmatched_pairs_all, 1, paste0, collapse="")                  %in% apply(ref, 1, paste0, collapse=""))/nP_all  cat("threshold: ", threshold,       "
nb matched: ", nP_all,"; nb true matches: ", nTM_all,       "
TPR: ", TPR_all, ";   PPV: ", PPV_all, "

", sep="") } print.res_matching(res_match_6y) print.res_matching(res_match_11y)  }

text: match_prob matching probabilities matrix (e.g. obtained recordLink) dimensions n1 x n2. y response variable length n1. binary phenotypes supported moment. x matrix data.frame predictors dimensions n2 x p. intercept automatically added within function. covar matrix data.frame variables adjusted test dimensions n3 x p. Either "best" (case highest probable match threshold imputed) "weighted average" (case weighted mean imputed individual least one match posterior probability threshold). Default "weighted average".

code: estep_vect <- function(ag_score, p, m, u){   a <-exp(log(p) + ag_score%*%log(m) + (1-ag_score)%*%log(1-m))   b <- exp(log(1-p) + ag_score%*%log(u) + (1-ag_score)%*%log(1-u))   return(cbind(a/(a+b), b/(a+b))) }

text: data1 either binary (1 0 values ) matrix binary data frame dimension n1 x K whose rownames observation identifiers. data2 either binary (1 0 values ) matrix binary data frame dimension n2 x K whose rownames observation identifiers. Columns order data1. dates1 matrix dataframe dimension n1 x K including concatenated dates intervals corresponding diagnosis codes data1. Default NULL case dates used. dates2 matrix dataframe dimension n2 x K including concatenated dates intervals corresponding diagnosis codes data2. Default NULL case dates used. See details. eps_plus discrepancy rate data1 data2 eps_minus discrepancy rate data2 data1 aggreg_2ways character string indicating merge posterior two probability matrices obtained 2 databases. Four possibility currently implemented: "maxnorm", "max", "min", "mean" "prod". Default "mean". min_prev minimum prevalence variables used matching. Default 1%. data1_cont2diff either matrix dataframe continuous features, age, similarity measure uses difference data2_cont2diff, whose rownames . Default NULL. data2_cont2diff either matrix dataframe continuous features, age, similarity measure uses difference data2_cont1diff, whose rownames . Default NULL. d_max numeric vector length K giving minimum difference considered discrepancy. use_diff logical flag indicating whether continuous differentiable variables used

title: Probabilistic Patient Record Linkage — recordLink
code: set.seed(123) ncodes <- 500 npat <- 200 incid <- abs(rnorm(n=ncodes, 0.15, 0.07)) bin_codes <- rbinom(n=npat*ncodes, size=1,  prob=rep(incid, npat)) bin_codes_mat <- matrix(bin_codes, ncol=ncodes, byrow = TRUE) data1_ex <- bin_codes_mat[1:(npat/2+npat/10),] data2_ex <- bin_codes_mat[c(1:(npat/10), (npat/2+npat/10 + 1):npat), ] rownames(data1_ex) <- paste0("ID", 1:(npat/2+npat/10), "_data1") rownames(data2_ex) <- paste0("ID", c(1:(npat/10), (npat/2+npat/10 + 1):npat), "_data2")  if(interactive()){ res <- recordLink(data1 = data1_ex, data2 = data2_ex,                   use_diff = FALSE, eps_minus = 0.01, eps_plus = 0.01) round(res[c(1:3, 19:23), c(1:3, 19:23)], 3) }
